TY  - JOUR
T1  - Agency and Transaction Cost Perspectives on the Manager-Shareholder Relationship: Incentives for Congruent Interests
AU  - Oviatt, Benjamin M.
Y1  - 1988/04/01
PY  - 1988
DA  - 1988/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1988.4306868
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1988.4306868
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 214
EP  - 225
VL  - 13
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This paper examines the manager-shareholder relationship through agency and transaction cost theories. The literature of those theories suggests several incentives and monitoring methods that may control opportunistic behavior among managers. Ten hypotheses are proposed concerning those incentives and monitoring methods, and methodological suggestions are made to motivate research regarding the congruence of managerial and shareholder interests.
AB  - This paper examines the manager-shareholder relationship through agency and transaction cost theories. The literature of those theories suggests several incentives and monitoring methods that may control opportunistic behavior among managers. Ten hypotheses are proposed concerning those incentives and monitoring methods, and methodological suggestions are made to motivate research regarding the congruence of managerial and shareholder interests.
