JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 287
EP  - 301
VL  - 13
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Control is defined as the cybernetic regulation of iterative activity within dependence relationships. This framework is used to examine critical aspects of control and its initiation. Two quasi-control responses, dependence reduction and dependence restructuring, are proposed and discussed. Implications of the framework for research and managerial practice are discussed.
AB  - Control is defined as the cybernetic regulation of iterative activity within dependence relationships. This framework is used to examine critical aspects of control and its initiation. Two quasi-control responses, dependence reduction and dependence restructuring, are proposed and discussed. Implications of the framework for research and managerial practice are discussed.
